14 NEW SECTION. SECTION 1. LOCAL GOVERNMENT LARGE TAXPAYER RESERVE ACCOUNT -- EXPENDITURE
15 RESTRICTIONS. (1) THE GOVERNING BODY OF A CITY, COUNTY, OR CONSOLIDATED CITY-COUNTY MAY ESTABLISH A
16 LARGE TAXPAYER RESERVE ACCOUNT.
17 (2) (a) A CITY, COUNTY, OR CONSOLIDATED CITY-COUNTY THAT ESTABLISHES AN ACCOUNT PURSUANT TO
18 THIS SECTION SHALL DEPOSIT ANNUALLY 10% OF REVENUE GENERATED FROM NEWLY TAXABLE PROPERTY IN CLASSES
19 OTHER THAN CLASS FOUR IN THE LARGE TAXPAYER RESERVE ACCOUNT.
20 (b) A city or consolidated city-county that establishes an account pursuant to this section shall
21 deposit annually in the account 10% of revenue generated from newly taxable property in classes other than
22 class four and from newly taxable class four residential property.
23 (3) A CITY, COUNTY, OR CONSOLIDATED CITY-COUNTY MAY USE A PORTION OF THE REVENUE FROM NEWLY
24 TAXABLE PROPERTY GENERATED UNDER SUBSECTION (2) TO OFFSET ANY REQUIRED PAYMENT TO THE DEPARTMENT FOR
25 TECHNOLOGY ENHANCING THE ASSESSMENT OF NEWLY TAXABLE PROPERTY.
26 (4) SUBJECT TO A PAYMENT MADE PURSUANT TO SUBSECTION (3), MONEY DEPOSITED IN THE ACCOUNT BY
27 THE CITY, COUNTY, OR CONSOLIDATED CITY-COUNTY MUST REMAIN IN THE ACCOUNT AND MAY NOT BE APPROPRIATED BY
