19 ACCOUNT NOT SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (3) FOR THE PURPOSES PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (5).
20 (8) AS USED IN THIS SECTION, THE FOLLOWING DEFINITIONS APPLY:
21 (A) "LARGE TAXPAYER" MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL OR ENTITY WITH TAXABLE VALUE FOR ALL PROPERTY OWNED
22 BY THE INDIVIDUAL OR ENTITY WITHIN THE CITY, COUNTY, OR CONSOLIDATED CITY-COUNTY THAT PLACES THE INDIVIDUAL
23 OR ENTITY AMONG THE 20% OF TAXPAYERS WITH THE LARGEST TAXABLE VALUE IN THE CITY, COUNTY, OR
24 CONSOLIDATED CITY-COUNTY.
25 (B) "SIGNIFICANT DECREASE IN TAXABLE VALUE" MEANS A DECREASE IN TAXABLE VALUE FOR PROPERTY
26 CLASSES OTHER THAN CLASS FOUR PROPERTY THAT EQUALS 25% OR MORE OF THE PRIOR YEAR'S TAXABLE VALUE.
